1
00:00:00,915 --> 00:00:03,603
I made them leave

2
00:00:03,603 --> 00:00:06,390
because I wanted to be alone with you.

3
00:00:23,293 --> 00:00:26,012
It gets noisy when there are other people.

4
00:00:26,012 --> 00:00:28,522
That's why I avoided cafés.

5
00:00:28,522 --> 00:00:32,581
The study rooms at the library were fully booked already.

6
00:00:34,299 --> 00:00:36,349
That's why.

7
00:00:37,686 --> 00:00:41,368
I feel a bit awkward

8
00:00:41,368 --> 00:00:47,523
to be alone with you too, but I don't hate it.

9
00:00:47,523 --> 00:00:51,197
I actually like it somewhat.

10
00:01:07,359 --> 00:01:12,159
[Best Make 3]

11
00:01:13,199 --> 00:01:15,316
Our photo Club Moment is going on a camping trip!

12
00:01:15,316 --> 00:01:17,382
Make some noise!

13
00:01:19,314 --> 00:01:20,294
Alright.

14
00:01:20,294 --> 00:01:23,280
Let's get into groups to prepare everything we need for the camp.

15
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:25,079
We're going to have an accommodation reservation team,

16
00:01:25,079 --> 00:01:28,513
a transportation team, and a grocery shopping team.

17
00:01:29,929 --> 00:01:31,459
Let's play Ghost Leg again to decide—

18
00:01:31,459 --> 00:01:33,404
Mr. President!

19
00:01:33,404 --> 00:01:35,045
What's with you playing Ghost Leg again?

20
00:01:35,045 --> 00:01:37,559
It took ages last time.

21
00:01:37,559 --> 00:01:41,157
Let's just use the app.

22
00:01:41,157 --> 00:01:42,894
- But—
- Mr. President!

23
00:01:42,894 --> 00:01:45,087
I'll make them.

24
00:01:49,056 --> 00:01:50,654
[Accommodation Team: Ye Seok, Se Hui]
[Transport Team: Jin Hyeok, Mun Hui]

25
00:01:50,654 --> 00:01:51,597
The teams are

26
00:01:51,629 --> 00:01:52,697
[Grocery Shopping Team: Hyeon Ho, Yeon Du]

27
00:01:52,722 --> 00:01:54,770
made like this.

28
00:01:57,576 --> 00:02:00,385
Please check if it's correct.

29
00:02:00,385 --> 00:02:03,540
[Grocery shopping]

30
00:02:05,126 --> 00:02:08,090
[Grocery shopping]

31
00:02:10,386 --> 00:02:13,960
[Accommodation reservation]

32
00:02:17,177 --> 00:02:20,680
[Accommodation reservation]

33
00:02:27,888 --> 00:02:30,599
Is everything correct?

34
00:02:31,431 --> 00:02:33,596
Yes.

35
00:02:33,596 --> 00:02:35,573
Yes, it is.

36
00:02:42,438 --> 00:02:43,130
Then,

37
00:02:43,402 --> 00:02:44,779
it's now been confirmed.

38
00:03:00,325 --> 00:03:02,003
It's your turn to wait for me now.

39
00:03:02,003 --> 00:03:04,539
Like how I did for you.

40
00:03:04,539 --> 00:03:07,160
Now it's your turn to have a crush on me.

41
00:03:08,821 --> 00:03:12,179
What did she mean by that?

42
00:03:14,066 --> 00:03:16,319
What does she want me to do?

43
00:03:22,443 --> 00:03:25,447
[Unrequited love]

44
00:03:25,447 --> 00:03:28,878
Love that is not reciprocated by the beloved.

45
00:03:29,975 --> 00:03:32,873
So here, I'm on one side

46
00:03:32,873 --> 00:03:35,234
and Seol is on the other.

47
00:03:35,234 --> 00:03:39,520
So it means, only I like her,

48
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:43,581
but she doesn't like me back.

49
00:03:48,843 --> 00:03:51,083
Was it her subtle way of saying no?

50
00:03:51,083 --> 00:03:53,457
She wants me to have a crush on her.

51
00:03:53,457 --> 00:03:56,543
What? What did you say?

52
00:03:59,636 --> 00:04:01,477
I've told you already.

53
00:04:01,477 --> 00:04:02,782
A crush.

54
00:04:02,782 --> 00:04:04,769
Having a crush.

55
00:04:04,769 --> 00:04:06,164
Ju Ho has a crush on you, Seol?

56
00:04:06,164 --> 00:04:08,183
- Yes.
- I mean...

57
00:04:08,183 --> 00:04:11,262
You two would have dated each other a million times by now.

58
00:04:11,262 --> 00:04:13,338
A crush? Out of nowhere?

59
00:04:13,338 --> 00:04:15,294
Was it his idea?

60
00:04:15,294 --> 00:04:18,396
Has he gone lukewarm, saying he'd have a crush on you?

61
00:04:18,396 --> 00:04:20,827
No, that's not it.

62
00:04:21,657 --> 00:04:25,278
I told him to have a crush on me.

63
00:04:25,278 --> 00:04:27,191
Why?

64
00:04:34,565 --> 00:04:37,100
Because I wanted to see if he's serious.

65
00:04:38,516 --> 00:04:40,460
You're something else.

66
00:04:40,460 --> 00:04:43,280
You told him to have a crush on you?

67
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:46,575
Yeah, she's something else.

68
00:04:47,823 --> 00:04:51,386
Wait, would that be enough though?

69
00:04:51,386 --> 00:04:53,618
He's only doing it because you made him to.

70
00:04:53,618 --> 00:04:55,477
I know but—

71
00:04:55,477 --> 00:04:57,626
I'll help you.

72
00:04:58,683 --> 00:05:00,078
Lipstick?

73
00:05:00,078 --> 00:05:02,774
Lipstick? Who's that?

74
00:05:03,961 --> 00:05:05,700
What's going on?

75
00:05:07,590 --> 00:05:09,001
I'm sorry for eavesdropping.

76
00:05:09,001 --> 00:05:11,108
I didn't mean to eavesdrop.

77
00:05:12,810 --> 00:05:17,154
Your friend's voice was so loud, that I couldn't help but overhear.

78
00:05:17,154 --> 00:05:21,195
By the way, what do you mean you want to help?

79
00:05:21,845 --> 00:05:25,039
You said you wanted to check how serious Seo Ju Ho was about you.

80
00:05:25,039 --> 00:05:28,261
I'll help you with that.

81
00:05:29,334 --> 00:05:32,365
I mean, how will you?

82
00:05:32,365 --> 00:05:33,625
Why would you help me with that?

83
00:05:33,625 --> 00:05:35,332
Sorry?

84
00:05:35,332 --> 00:05:37,612
By chance, do you like me?

85
00:05:41,895 --> 00:05:44,816
- Yes.
- Sorry?

86
00:05:44,816 --> 00:05:46,665
I have a crush on you.

87
00:05:48,123 --> 00:05:51,557
Ever since I saw you,

88
00:05:52,853 --> 00:05:54,844
I've had a crush on you.

89
00:05:59,917 --> 00:06:01,450
Well,

90
00:06:01,450 --> 00:06:03,702
- excuse me—
- So,

91
00:06:04,543 --> 00:06:06,545
just use me.

92
00:06:08,764 --> 00:06:11,135
I'll let you use me.

93
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:16,810
Well, it would be nice if you gave me a chance

94
00:06:16,810 --> 00:06:19,150
when you get some time while using me.

95
00:06:27,399 --> 00:06:30,279
What's going on? Why didn't Yu Seol tell me?

96
00:06:30,279 --> 00:06:31,070
Did you know?

97
00:06:31,070 --> 00:06:32,312
No, I didn't.

98
00:06:32,312 --> 00:06:34,374
It's so exciting.

99
00:06:39,052 --> 00:06:41,274
It's been a while.

100
00:06:44,835 --> 00:06:46,525
Remember that time?

101
00:06:46,525 --> 00:06:48,993
You were busy with an assignment all night and you even skipped dinner,

102
00:06:48,993 --> 00:06:51,413
so I came to cook dinner for you.

103
00:06:51,413 --> 00:06:53,176
I came here to shop for groceries at the time

104
00:06:53,176 --> 00:06:56,002
because it was the only store that was open late.

105
00:07:07,962 --> 00:07:10,309
Here you go.

106
00:07:12,039 --> 00:07:13,574
Wow, it looks so yummy.

107
00:07:13,574 --> 00:07:15,963
Thank you.

108
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:26,280
It's so good. You're the best.

109
00:07:33,110 --> 00:07:34,495
Chew well and eat slowly.

110
00:07:34,495 --> 00:07:36,777
I'll make you some more if you want.

111
00:07:39,853 --> 00:07:44,374
By the way, what if I get chubby after eating all this?

112
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:48,670
Why is everything yummy so high in calories?

113
00:07:48,670 --> 00:07:50,612
It's okay to put on some weight.

114
00:07:50,612 --> 00:07:53,728
Squirtle, you're going to be pretty no matter what.

115
00:07:54,471 --> 00:07:56,846
This is so yummy.

116
00:07:56,846 --> 00:07:58,557
I'll cook something even better next time.

117
00:07:58,557 --> 00:08:01,561
I'm developing a recipe.

118
00:08:01,561 --> 00:08:04,835
Oh, right. I've got something for you too.

119
00:08:07,381 --> 00:08:08,254
Ta-da!

120
00:08:08,254 --> 00:08:10,543
Our matching backpacks.

121
00:08:10,543 --> 00:08:13,700
You always carry around your cookbook and utensils.

122
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:15,444
You can put them all in this bag now.

123
00:08:15,444 --> 00:08:18,810
It's really light and comfortable.

124
00:08:18,810 --> 00:08:20,062
Thanks.

125
00:08:20,062 --> 00:08:22,190
- Can I see it?
- Sure.

126
00:08:23,663 --> 00:08:25,510
So cute.

127
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:27,135
- Right?
- Yes.

128
00:08:27,135 --> 00:08:29,150
I picked it myself.

129
00:08:29,150 --> 00:08:31,887
- Let me try it on.
- Go ahead.

130
00:08:33,731 --> 00:08:34,805
- How do I look?
- Nice.

131
00:08:34,805 --> 00:08:36,599
Does it look good on me?

132
00:08:37,336 --> 00:08:39,591
Oh? The size is perfect for my back.

133
00:08:39,591 --> 00:08:42,101
I know, right? So comfortable, right?

134
00:08:44,162 --> 00:08:45,862
- So are we going to wear matching bags?
- Yes!

135
00:08:45,862 --> 00:08:49,300
Mine is white and yours is black.

136
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:51,858
I used to come here often.

137
00:08:53,772 --> 00:08:56,727
Bell peppers. Should we get some?

138
00:08:58,249 --> 00:09:00,970
Let's get it done quickly and get out.

139
00:09:16,371 --> 00:09:18,273
How about this place?

140
00:09:18,273 --> 00:09:21,216
The size of the rooms are alright and the location isn't bad.

141
00:09:21,216 --> 00:09:24,034
Save it and ask the president later.

142
00:09:25,752 --> 00:09:27,375
Okay.

143
00:09:34,766 --> 00:09:37,889
You know we went somewhere similar.

144
00:09:39,472 --> 00:09:42,125
Remember the trip we went on our 100th day anniversary?

145
00:09:42,125 --> 00:09:43,662
The accommodation was so nice.

146
00:09:43,662 --> 00:09:45,781
It was pretty and clean.

147
00:09:47,650 --> 00:09:50,301
There were a lot of bugs, though.

148
00:09:50,301 --> 00:09:55,444
You were so surprised by me yelling and crying

149
00:09:55,444 --> 00:09:58,354
because of the huge bug.

150
00:09:59,434 --> 00:10:02,480
It was so scary then,

151
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:07,070
but looking back, that was a good memory,

152
00:10:07,070 --> 00:10:08,845
wasn't it?

153
00:10:13,258 --> 00:10:15,619
I miss those days.

154
00:10:16,379 --> 00:10:19,929
I told you that I erased it all.

155
00:10:21,585 --> 00:10:24,971
So quit talking crap in front of me.

156
00:10:26,151 --> 00:10:30,979
It's a good memory for you but not for me.

157
00:10:32,205 --> 00:10:34,149
Ye Seok, I...

158
00:10:34,149 --> 00:10:36,616
Give me a break.

159
00:10:36,616 --> 00:10:39,347
I'm about to get uncomfortable.

160
00:10:41,414 --> 00:10:44,159
Let's just look it up separately.

161
00:11:09,397 --> 00:11:12,984
Why are you putting that in the cart? You can't even eat spicy food.

162
00:11:14,486 --> 00:11:17,763
You always get a stomachache from anything that's even slightly spicy.

163
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:21,694
There will be some people who like spicy food.

164
00:11:21,694 --> 00:11:24,785
So what? You can't eat it, anyway.

165
00:11:27,971 --> 00:11:33,429
I mean, it doesn't matter whether you can't have it.

166
00:11:33,429 --> 00:11:35,492
On top of that, technically,

167
00:11:35,492 --> 00:11:37,571
it's not that you can't have broccoli.

168
00:11:37,571 --> 00:11:40,913
You just don't eat it because you're a picky eater.

169
00:11:40,913 --> 00:11:42,939
You should have balanced meals

170
00:11:42,939 --> 00:11:44,098
when you're growing up.

171
00:11:44,098 --> 00:11:46,933
It's not good for you to eat only what you want.

172
00:11:46,933 --> 00:11:49,525
You're the one to talk.

173
00:11:49,525 --> 00:11:52,141
You don't eat cucumbers.

174
00:11:53,207 --> 00:11:56,410
Hey, that's not the same.

175
00:11:56,410 --> 00:11:57,342
Cucumbers are different.

176
00:11:57,367 --> 00:11:58,866
When it comes to cucumbers,

177
00:11:58,866 --> 00:12:00,952
there are strong likes and dislikes and you have to respect that.

178
00:12:00,952 --> 00:12:02,783
You've never heard of People Who Hate Cucumbers?

179
00:12:02,783 --> 00:12:05,724
How about Cucumber Psychopath, huh?

180
00:12:06,441 --> 00:12:08,933
It's the same with broccoli.

181
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:11,117
Stop talking back to me.

182
00:12:11,117 --> 00:12:12,182
You stop it, first.

183
00:12:12,182 --> 00:12:13,864
- No, you first.
- I don't want to.

184
00:12:13,864 --> 00:12:14,971
- Me, neither.
- No, no, no, no, no, no.

185
00:12:14,971 --> 00:12:16,358
I hate it more than you do. I hate it more than you do.

186
00:12:16,358 --> 00:12:20,160
- I don't want to.
- Me, neither! Me, neither! Me, neither!

187
00:12:27,408 --> 00:12:29,983
No more picky eating.

188
00:12:31,472 --> 00:12:34,086
You'll have a balanced meal today.

189
00:12:35,938 --> 00:12:37,453
It's all because of you.

190
00:12:37,453 --> 00:12:39,737
You started it.

191
00:12:47,995 --> 00:12:52,879
Mom, it's just a tattoo.

192
00:12:52,879 --> 00:12:55,264
Also I didn't run away because I was told by Dad.

193
00:12:55,264 --> 00:12:58,057
I just really wanted to get a tattoo.

194
00:13:02,658 --> 00:13:04,564
I know.

195
00:13:04,564 --> 00:13:07,545
Mom, I'm not that naive.

196
00:13:07,545 --> 00:13:11,777
I can take care of myself. Don't worry.

197
00:13:11,777 --> 00:13:14,610
Mom, I'll call you later.

198
00:13:14,610 --> 00:13:16,400
Okay.

199
00:13:19,031 --> 00:13:21,040
I can take care of myself.

200
00:13:25,406 --> 00:13:26,230
Excuse me.

201
00:13:26,230 --> 00:13:27,620
- Hello.
- Hello.

202
00:13:27,620 --> 00:13:29,090
Oh, hello.

203
00:13:30,490 --> 00:13:34,413
Do you have a second to talk about something important?

204
00:13:34,413 --> 00:13:35,474
Oh, sure.

205
00:13:35,474 --> 00:13:37,792
We're not weird people.

206
00:13:37,792 --> 00:13:40,876
We're just doing some research about young people these days

207
00:13:40,876 --> 00:13:42,583
by conducting a questionnaire.

208
00:13:42,583 --> 00:13:45,792
It's easy and it won't take long.

209
00:13:45,792 --> 00:13:49,485
Could you come with us just for a second?

210
00:13:50,164 --> 00:13:51,822
A questionnaire?

211
00:13:51,822 --> 00:13:54,409
You give a good first impression.

212
00:13:54,409 --> 00:13:56,762
Your face radiates light.

213
00:13:56,762 --> 00:13:59,199
I'm sure you get that a lot, right?

214
00:13:59,199 --> 00:14:00,775
No, it's my first time.

215
00:14:00,775 --> 00:14:01,706
Maybe it's because it's dark here.

216
00:14:01,706 --> 00:14:02,970
No, that's not it.

217
00:14:02,970 --> 00:14:05,712
I'm sure you get that a lot.

218
00:14:05,712 --> 00:14:07,659
It looks like you haven't got that before.

219
00:14:07,659 --> 00:14:10,216
But you have this bright light coming out of you,

220
00:14:10,216 --> 00:14:12,603
that can be seen only by people who have trained their mind.

221
00:14:12,603 --> 00:14:14,061
You're dazzling.

222
00:14:14,061 --> 00:14:18,211
It's all thanks to the good deeds of your ancestors.

223
00:14:18,211 --> 00:14:19,896
We don't offer this normally,

224
00:14:19,896 --> 00:14:21,503
but we want to give you an opportunity

225
00:14:21,503 --> 00:14:25,881
to say thank you to your ancestors for their good deeds.

226
00:14:25,881 --> 00:14:30,198
So are you willing to pray to your ancestors now?

227
00:14:30,198 --> 00:14:31,735
Are you free?

228
00:14:31,735 --> 00:14:33,308
My ancestors?

229
00:14:33,308 --> 00:14:35,924
It only takes 20 minutes. It's easy.

230
00:14:35,924 --> 00:14:37,885
There is our study room nearby.

231
00:14:37,885 --> 00:14:39,809
It's not dodgy or scary.

232
00:14:39,809 --> 00:14:41,886
It's a holy place where we hold a memorial service

233
00:14:41,886 --> 00:14:44,018
for our ancestors, wearing hanbok.

234
00:14:44,018 --> 00:14:45,808
- So you've never prayed
- Seo Ju Ho?

235
00:14:45,808 --> 00:14:46,735
to your ancestors

236
00:14:46,767 --> 00:14:48,892
- before, right?
- No.

237
00:14:48,892 --> 00:14:53,135
In this case, you can end up ruining both yourself and your family,

238
00:14:53,135 --> 00:14:55,677
sudden death, having a sudden urge to take a shit,

239
00:14:55,677 --> 00:14:57,048
losing your house,

240
00:14:57,048 --> 00:14:59,755
and so on.

241
00:14:59,755 --> 00:15:01,053
What should I do?

242
00:15:01,053 --> 00:15:02,500
Just come with us.

243
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:04,856
All you have to do is just bow, following our directions.

244
00:15:04,856 --> 00:15:06,149
Do you have a lot of cash on you?

245
00:15:06,149 --> 00:15:08,051
Just think of it as an opportunity to get good energy.

246
00:15:08,051 --> 00:15:09,731
- Oh.
- Yes.

247
00:15:09,731 --> 00:15:11,601
Seo Ju Ho!

248
00:15:13,072 --> 00:15:15,113
Do you know her?

249
00:15:18,601 --> 00:15:20,713
This is driving me crazy.

250
00:15:22,801 --> 00:15:23,983
Step aside.

251
00:15:23,983 --> 00:15:27,012
Hey. What are you pulling here? Huh?

252
00:15:27,012 --> 00:15:29,609
Why on earth did you mention his life would be ruined, doing a questionnaire?

253
00:15:29,609 --> 00:15:32,025
What's with the praying to the ancestors?

254
00:15:32,025 --> 00:15:34,021
I think you've misunderstood us.

255
00:15:34,021 --> 00:15:36,202
We're not weird people.

256
00:15:36,202 --> 00:15:39,209
We're just students who study the mind through the truth of the universe.

257
00:15:39,209 --> 00:15:41,827
Yes. Calm down a little bit.

258
00:15:41,827 --> 00:15:43,426
It looks like you two are friends.

259
00:15:43,426 --> 00:15:46,439
You also radiate bright light.

260
00:15:46,439 --> 00:15:50,169
If you pray to your ancestors as well, that will create a synergy effect.

261
00:15:50,169 --> 00:15:53,402
No, thanks. I don't want to pray to my ancestors.

262
00:15:53,402 --> 00:15:54,948
Who do you think you are?

263
00:15:54,948 --> 00:15:55,858
Let's go.

264
00:15:55,858 --> 00:15:57,757
Your friend was in the middle of talking to us.

265
00:15:57,757 --> 00:16:00,203
- You can't just take him like that.
- Bye.

266
00:16:00,203 --> 00:16:01,641
Your ancestors will get mad.

267
00:16:01,641 --> 00:16:04,027
- You were supposed to help me.
- Sorry.

268
00:16:04,027 --> 00:16:06,750
You should've blocked them from leaving.

269
00:16:08,914 --> 00:16:10,438
Excuse me.

270
00:16:10,438 --> 00:16:11,755
Oh, hello.

271
00:16:11,755 --> 00:16:15,086
Do you have a second to talk about something important?

272
00:16:15,086 --> 00:16:17,236
Of course. I have a lot of time.

273
00:16:17,236 --> 00:16:18,787
That's good.

274
00:16:18,787 --> 00:16:20,479
It's just that you give a good first impression.

275
00:16:20,479 --> 00:16:24,017
Oh, I think you give an even better first impression.

276
00:16:24,017 --> 00:16:25,324
Oh, thanks.

277
00:16:25,324 --> 00:16:27,092
Your face radiates bright light.

278
00:16:27,092 --> 00:16:28,913
That's not important.

279
00:16:28,913 --> 00:16:31,643
Could you fill out a simple questionnaire,

280
00:16:31,643 --> 00:16:33,708
- for us?
- I'll do that for you,

281
00:16:33,708 --> 00:16:36,515
over there. I've prepared a good thing for you.

282
00:16:36,515 --> 00:16:38,140
- Let's go.
- You've prepared it?

283
00:16:38,140 --> 00:16:39,060
What did you prepare?

284
00:16:39,060 --> 00:16:40,120
It's a good place.

285
00:16:40,145 --> 00:16:41,301
Coffee is on me.

286
00:16:41,301 --> 00:16:43,298
No, we have to...

287
00:16:43,298 --> 00:16:45,694
Are you stupid?

288
00:16:45,694 --> 00:16:48,309
Why were you even listening to what they were saying?

289
00:16:48,309 --> 00:16:50,340
You're right.

290
00:16:50,340 --> 00:16:52,551
I think I'm stupid.

291
00:16:52,551 --> 00:16:55,964
No, that's not what I meant.

292
00:16:55,964 --> 00:17:01,049
I thought I would be able to do everything by myself once I turned 20,

293
00:17:02,161 --> 00:17:04,574
but I was wrong.

294
00:17:04,574 --> 00:17:07,104
I'm just one year older but I'm the same.

295
00:17:07,866 --> 00:17:10,663
I feel like only you've become an adult but not me.

296
00:17:10,663 --> 00:17:13,133
I feel like I'm still the same high school student.

297
00:17:14,306 --> 00:17:17,433
I can't get anything right, except studying.

298
00:17:18,159 --> 00:17:19,878
What are you talking about?

299
00:17:19,878 --> 00:17:22,208
I feel the same as you.

300
00:17:23,067 --> 00:17:25,495
Nothing is easy for me.

301
00:17:25,495 --> 00:17:29,421
Everything is new and tough.

302
00:17:29,421 --> 00:17:34,281
But I think that's how it's supposed to be.

303
00:17:34,281 --> 00:17:36,102
You think?

304
00:17:36,102 --> 00:17:37,914
I mean, just because we become 20 years old,

305
00:17:37,914 --> 00:17:42,300
it's not like we start being adults who are ready from this point.

306
00:17:42,300 --> 00:17:44,532
Aren't we all supposed to go through trials and errors like this,

307
00:17:44,532 --> 00:17:46,341
to grow into adults?

308
00:17:46,341 --> 00:17:48,657
Just one step at a time.

309
00:17:52,801 --> 00:17:57,354
That's really comforting.

310
00:17:57,354 --> 00:17:58,934
Really?

311
00:17:59,752 --> 00:18:01,606
That's good.

312
00:18:06,859 --> 00:18:09,656
Why does he still remember what type of ramyun I like?

313
00:18:09,656 --> 00:18:11,116
That's such a minor thing.

314
00:18:11,116 --> 00:18:13,568
He's making me confused.

315
00:18:14,965 --> 00:18:17,058
I will eat spicy ramyun from now on.

316
00:18:17,058 --> 00:18:18,747
It's just that I haven't had it a lot.

317
00:18:18,747 --> 00:18:21,188
I can eat it if I try.

318
00:18:22,638 --> 00:18:24,925
You skipped dinner?

319
00:18:27,278 --> 00:18:29,702
I did, too.

320
00:18:29,702 --> 00:18:33,318
You must've been busy, skipping dinner like that.

321
00:18:33,318 --> 00:18:36,857
Well, it just happened that way.

322
00:18:38,855 --> 00:18:42,518
How was the grocery shopping?

323
00:18:42,518 --> 00:18:45,336
Well, it was okay.

324
00:18:49,141 --> 00:18:50,610
How about you?

325
00:18:50,610 --> 00:18:55,340
Was it okay with Se Hui?

326
00:18:56,448 --> 00:18:58,996
Why wouldn't it be?

327
00:18:59,971 --> 00:19:02,420
We're history.

328
00:19:08,364 --> 00:19:10,375
It must've been tough on you, though.

329
00:19:10,375 --> 00:19:11,379
No.

330
00:19:11,379 --> 00:19:14,477
I didn't feel a thing, either. I mean it.

331
00:19:15,427 --> 00:19:18,550
Eat the ramyun before it gets soggy.

332
00:19:30,841 --> 00:19:33,394
Spicy. Spicy.

333
00:19:39,380 --> 00:19:41,746
It really tastes like hell.

334
00:19:42,798 --> 00:19:46,377
Have mine instead. It's not spicy.

335
00:19:46,377 --> 00:19:49,195
Do you like spicy food?

336
00:19:49,195 --> 00:19:52,139
I love spicy food.

337
00:19:52,881 --> 00:19:54,673
Oh, that's good then.

338
00:19:57,984 --> 00:20:00,146
Let me switch the chopsticks.

339
00:20:01,218 --> 00:20:02,911
Okay.

340
00:20:03,922 --> 00:20:05,617
Be careful. It's super spicy.

341
00:20:05,617 --> 00:20:08,380
No, I'm good. I enjoy spicy food.

342
00:20:16,040 --> 00:20:18,333
Are you okay?

343
00:20:18,333 --> 00:20:20,547
It's not because it's spicy.

344
00:20:20,547 --> 00:20:22,378
It's not spicy at all.

345
00:20:26,189 --> 00:20:28,271
Drink some water.

346
00:20:31,573 --> 00:20:34,106
- It's not spicy, right?
- No.

347
00:20:34,106 --> 00:20:35,354
Do you want to trade it back again?

348
00:20:35,354 --> 00:20:39,193
No, I'm good. I like this better.

349
00:20:39,193 --> 00:20:40,964
What's going on?

350
00:20:49,143 --> 00:20:52,141
So quit talking crap in front of me.

351
00:20:52,141 --> 00:20:56,518
It's a good memory for you but not for me.

352
00:20:57,216 --> 00:20:59,800
Did he have to be so brutal?

353
00:21:09,249 --> 00:21:13,030
[Final Application for Seattle Castla Overseas Internship]

354
00:21:17,300 --> 00:21:22,100
[Mom: It looks like you'll have to take a year off if you can't get a scholarship. I'm sorry.]

355
00:21:22,192 --> 00:21:25,970
[Hwayang University Business Management Freshman Do Ye Seok]

356
00:21:32,071 --> 00:21:33,976
Hey, did you hear that?

357
00:21:33,976 --> 00:21:38,013
Jin Se Hui got the overseas internship this year.

358
00:21:38,013 --> 00:21:40,728
Do Ye Seok helped her a lot with that. Did she backstab him?

359
00:21:40,728 --> 00:21:44,076
She totally used poor Do Ye Seok.

360
00:21:44,076 --> 00:21:45,324
Right.

361
00:21:45,324 --> 00:21:48,264
She has never been able to get a scholarship because of Do Ye Seok.

362
00:21:48,264 --> 00:21:51,166
It doesn't make sense that she got the internship all of a sudden.

363
00:21:51,166 --> 00:21:53,010
Seriously.

364
00:22:18,536 --> 00:22:20,480
Are you trying to get yourself killed?

365
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:24,018
What were you thinking? You could've gotten hurt!

366
00:22:32,765 --> 00:22:35,538
Hey, what's going on?

367
00:22:35,538 --> 00:22:37,385
Are you crying?

368
00:22:39,554 --> 00:22:42,874
I get that you got scared but it's not necessary to cry.

369
00:22:42,874 --> 00:22:44,366
I don't know.

370
00:22:44,366 --> 00:22:47,022
Stop talking to me. I'm embarrassed.

371
00:23:01,582 --> 00:23:05,563
Hey. Am I supposed to do these things for you because of the alliance now?

372
00:23:05,563 --> 00:23:07,844
You're annoying.

373
00:23:09,309 --> 00:23:14,054
You. Why do you keep being nice to me?

374
00:23:14,054 --> 00:23:15,753
What?

375
00:23:16,815 --> 00:23:19,007
What if

376
00:23:21,769 --> 00:23:24,580
I end up falling for you?

377
00:23:35,539 --> 00:23:38,924
[Best Mistake 3]

378
00:23:38,949 --> 00:23:42,980
[Bonus clip]

379
00:23:47,365 --> 00:23:49,414
Kim Yeon Du.

380
00:23:49,414 --> 00:23:53,358
That's not yours.

381
00:23:55,281 --> 00:23:56,057
Ta-da!

382
00:23:56,082 --> 00:23:58,622
Our matching backpacks!

383
00:23:58,622 --> 00:24:01,420
It's really light and comfortable.

384
00:24:10,810 --> 00:24:15,070
♫ The two of us that seems 100 percent close and perfect ♫

385
00:24:15,070 --> 00:24:16,537
[Next episode]
What are you guys doing here?

386
00:24:16,537 --> 00:24:18,541
Hyung Dae Yeong invited us.

387
00:24:18,541 --> 00:24:20,342
She's the only one who fell?

388
00:24:20,342 --> 00:24:21,402
I'll go then.

389
00:24:21,402 --> 00:24:22,451
I'll go.

390
00:24:22,451 --> 00:24:24,255
- Where's Yeon Du?
- Why are you coming back alone?

391
00:24:24,255 --> 00:24:25,555
Why didn't you pick up my call?

392
00:24:25,555 --> 00:24:27,105
Yeon Du!

393
00:24:27,105 --> 00:24:28,620
It drives me crazy.

394
00:24:28,620 --> 00:24:33,810
♫ Run faster toward me ♫

395
00:24:33,810 --> 00:24:37,170
♫ 100 percent between the two of us ♫

396
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:39,120
♫ Sometimes I know or don't know, it's strange ♫

397
00:24:39,120 --> 00:24:42,560
[Best Mistake 3]
